  description: Minokawa is described in Mindanao lore as an immense sky creature
    associated with consuming light and unsettling the balance of day and night.
    The figure carries apocalyptic undertones, often representing cosmic-scale threat
    rather than local haunting. In mythic interpretation, Minokawa embodies fear
    of celestial disorder and the fragility of natural cycles.
